        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 19 at 3:00PM CDT by NWS Austin/San Antonio TX</headline>
        <description>At 300 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Loma Alta, moving southwest at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Loma Alta, Devils Shores, Pafford Crossing, Vinegarone, Rough Canyon
Recreation Area, and Devils River State Nat Area Big Satan.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
